Requesterpool@jpdev.pro

Tested byTestaro, procedure ts24
Scored byTestilo, procedure tsp24
Digested byTestilo, procedure tdp24

Introduction

This is a digest of results from a battery of accessibility Tests.

The battery includes 1353 automated accessibility tests drawn from ten different packages: Alfa, Axe, Continuum, Equal Access, HTML CodeSniffer, Nu Html Checker, QualWeb, Tenon, Testaro, and WAVE.

These tests were run on the web page named above and gave the page a score of 1833, where 0 would be perfect.

Issue summary

Special issues

log: Score 398. This is based on the amount of browser error logging and miscellaneous logging during the tests.

solos: Score 16. This is based on issues reported by unclassified tests. Details are in the report.

Classified issues

Issue overflowHidden

WCAG: 1.4.4

Score: 152

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r83, score 16 (Overflow is hidden or clipped if the text is enlarged)
  • Package qualWeb, test QW-ACT-R40, score 144 (Zoomed text node is clipped by a CSS overflow declaration)

Issue textContrastAA

WCAG: 1.4.3

Score: 131

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r69, score 67 (Text outside widget has subminimum contrast)
  • Package axe, test color-contrast, score 50 (Element has insufficient color contrast)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AAA.1_4_6.G18.Fail, score 32 (Contrast between the text and its background is less than 4.5:1)
  • Package ibm, test IBMA_Color_Contrast_WCAG2AA, score 12 (Contrast ratio of text with background does not meet WCAG 2.1 AA)
  • Package qualWeb, test QW-ACT-R37, score 4 (Text has less than the minimum contrast)
  • Package wave, test c:contrast, score 57 (Very low contrast)
